Dad, it's for real this time!

19
00:01:58,130 --> 00:01:59,570
What?

20
00:02:03,090 --> 00:02:05,210
Hurry up!

21
00:02:10,370 --> 00:02:13,960
Hey, Jae Won! Jae Won!

22
00:02:19,230 --> 00:02:21,410
What's wrong?

23
00:02:21,410 --> 00:02:23,470
Why are you suddenly doing this?

24
00:02:23,470 --> 00:02:26,150
No. Let me drive. Let me drive.

25
00:02:26,150 --> 00:02:28,570
It's dangerous to drive now. Get in.

26
00:02:39,610 --> 00:02:45,440
Yes. Please go and check on Ah Rin first. Right now.

27
00:02:46,480 --> 00:02:48,760
What is it? What's going on?

28
00:02:48,760 --> 00:02:52,310
Hurry. Hurry. Hurry. Hurry!

29
00:03:03,750 --> 00:03:05,510
Hey, Jae Won!

30
00:03:13,500 --> 00:03:15,790
She's sleeping in the room.

31
00:03:57,000 --> 00:03:58,300
Yes.

32
00:03:59,530 --> 00:04:01,870
I came immediately when you called.

33
00:04:01,870 --> 00:04:03,850
It's been about 20 minutes.

34
00:04:03,850 --> 00:04:06,290
By chance, was someone else... Did you see anyone?

35
00:04:06,290 --> 00:04:08,680
It was just Ah Rin when I came.

36
00:04:08,680 --> 00:04:13,130
Looked like she fell asleep on the couch after playing.

37
00:04:13,130 --> 00:04:16,590
- It's your day off today. Thanks for coming.
- Not at all.

38
00:04:16,590 --> 00:04:18,800
- I think you can leave now.
- Okay.

39
00:04:20,420 --> 00:04:22,620
- Thank you.
- Sure.

40
00:04:32,700 --> 00:04:34,040
What is it?

41
00:04:34,740 --> 00:04:36,550
Talk to me now.

42
00:04:36,550 --> 00:04:38,310
What's going on?

43
00:04:39,960 --> 00:04:40,970
Jae Won.

44
00:04:40,970 --> 00:04:44,340
Why did you leave her alone?

45
00:04:44,340 --> 00:04:45,740
What?

46
00:04:48,770 --> 00:04:51,090
You're the one who texted me.

47
00:04:51,090 --> 00:04:55,230
You told me to come to the office immediately because you called the sitter, didn't you?

48
00:04:57,760 --> 00:04:59,170
What?

49
00:05:00,460 --> 00:05:02,640
Didn't you text me?

50
00:05:05,060 --> 00:05:07,190
W-What is it?

51
00:05:09,400 --> 00:05:12,030
We need to find him before it's too late.

52
00:05:12,030 --> 00:05:13,350
Find whom?

53
00:05:13,350 --> 00:05:16,250
Your older brother who went missing.

54
00:05:16,250 --> 00:05:17,560
Heo Chi Yeong?

55
00:05:17,560 --> 00:05:18,990
Have you talked to him recently?

56
00:05:18,990 --> 00:05:22,310
What's going on that you're bringing him up?

57
00:05:22,310 --> 00:05:23,670
When was the last time you talked to him?

58
00:05:23,670 --> 00:05:26,640
I don't know. I don't even remember.

59
00:05:26,640 --> 00:05:29,860
How come you never thought about looking for him?

60
00:05:30,930 --> 00:05:36,010
I haven't talked to him since I was 13, when my parents divorced. It's been 30 years since I talked to him.

61
00:05:36,010 --> 00:05:37,530
He's basically a stranger.

62
00:05:37,530 --> 00:05:39,110
But he's your family.

63
00:05:39,110 --> 00:05:40,630
Family?

64
00:05:41,760 --> 00:05:43,810
He's not my family.

65
00:05:43,810 --> 00:05:47,500
To me, my only family is you and Ah Rin.

66
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:52,920
What you just said...

67
00:05:54,440 --> 00:05:56,490
Don't ever forget it.

68
00:06:21,320 --> 00:06:24,980
My gosh. You're an amazing artist.

69
00:06:24,980 --> 00:06:26,330
Who's that?

70
00:06:27,130 --> 00:06:29,090
It's my daughter.

71
00:06:29,090 --> 00:06:31,270
She's so cute.

72
00:07:00,690 --> 00:07:06,400
Heo Chi Yeong? What's going on that you're bringing him up?

73
00:07:08,830 --> 00:07:10,920
[Nam Tae Joo]

74
00:07:14,300 --> 00:07:19,190
I requested Heo Chi Yeong's transaction and call history.

75
00:07:19,190 --> 00:07:23,310
I texted you his latest address, too.

76
00:07:23,310 --> 00:07:26,010
Will you go there yourself, by the way?

77
00:07:26,010 --> 00:07:27,860
Thank you.

78
00:07:31,640 --> 00:07:34,490
[511, Dojeong-ri, Amin-myeon, Jangseon-gun, Gangwon-do]

79
00:07:43,260 --> 00:07:45,060
Did you find anything?

80
00:07:46,500 --> 00:07:49,790
[Call Records]
Yes. I recovered the contacts and recent call records.

81
00:07:49,790 --> 00:07:51,920
And I found the number he called the most.

82
00:07:51,920 --> 00:07:54,120
- Who is it?
- The number isn't saved.

83
00:07:54,120 --> 00:07:55,950
He called a number that wasn't even saved?

84
00:07:55,950 --> 00:07:58,750
Recently and very frequently.

85
00:07:59,750 --> 00:08:03,560
Do we need to request to look up the number to find out who it is?

86
00:08:03,560 --> 00:08:07,010
You don't have to. I already found out.

87
00:08:08,840 --> 00:08:11,090
You save the phone number,

88
00:08:11,090 --> 00:08:15,180
check the messenger profile, and you get the name and photo.

89
00:08:15,180 --> 00:08:17,200
So easy.

90
00:08:19,480 --> 00:08:22,770
I know who you think it is. Ms. Seo's husband, Professor Heo Soon Yeong.

91
00:08:22,800 --> 00:08:27,390
But the name on the profile is Heo Chi Yeong.

92
00:08:27,390 --> 00:08:29,300
[Heo Chi Yeong]

93
00:08:31,300 --> 00:08:33,240
Something's fishy, right?

94
00:08:38,480 --> 00:08:43,390
Hello? Seung Gyu, what happened?

95
00:08:43,390 --> 00:08:45,940
I asked what happened? Why won't you answer?

96
00:08:46,660 --> 00:08:47,940
Baek Seung Gyu.

97
00:08:47,940 --> 00:08:51,170
As the technology continues to get developed,

98
00:08:51,170 --> 00:08:54,380
we won't stop researching integrated design.

99
00:08:54,410 --> 00:08:58,100
The man I'm seeing isn't Jae Won's husband.

100
00:08:58,100 --> 00:09:00,490
It's his twin brother.

101
00:09:02,450 --> 00:09:04,160
Heo Chi Yeong.

102
00:09:29,810 --> 00:09:31,660
Excuse me.

103
00:09:57,240 --> 00:09:59,160
[Water and sewage bill]

104
00:09:59,160 --> 00:10:01,820
Nobody lives there.

105
00:10:03,130 --> 00:10:04,950
Hello.

106
00:10:07,410 --> 00:10:11,550
Do you know Heo Chi Yeong, who used to live here?

107
00:10:11,550 --> 00:10:14,900
Do you mean the young man who used to live here?

108
00:10:16,680 --> 00:10:18,820
He looks like this.

109
00:10:19,820 --> 00:10:21,690
Yes, that's him.

110
00:10:21,690 --> 00:10:23,290
Is he your husband?

111
00:10:23,290 --> 00:10:25,940
He said he wasn't married.

112
00:10:25,940 --> 00:10:27,350
Do you know where he went?

113
00:10:27,350 --> 00:10:29,720
I haven't seen him in a while.

114
00:10:29,720 --> 00:10:33,580
Some say he went to a big hospital because he's sick.

115
00:10:33,580 --> 00:10:37,720
Right. Stop by Seorin Hospital at the intersection downtown.

116
00:10:37,720 --> 00:10:39,780
He went there often.

117
00:10:39,780 --> 00:10:42,210
Okay. Thank you.

118
00:10:48,310 --> 00:10:51,150
- Hello?
- Mom, I'm sick.

119
00:10:51,150 --> 00:10:54,590
Ah Rin. Where does it hurt? Where's Dad?

120
00:10:54,590 --> 00:10:57,940
They say depression is the heart's cold in modern society.

121
00:10:57,940 --> 00:11:01,870
That's right. A lot of people don't know about bipolar disorder.

122
00:11:01,870 --> 00:11:04,970
Dr. Jo Soo Gyeong, could you explain in detail?

123
00:11:04,970 --> 00:11:07,780
Yes. Bipolar disorder.

124
00:11:07,780 --> 00:11:11,430
It's also commonly known as manic depressive disorder.

125
00:11:11,430 --> 00:11:17,460
It's a mood disorder in which you feel elevated and down back to back repeatedly.

126
00:11:17,460 --> 00:11:21,970
It can change your mood several times a day when it's severe.

127
00:11:21,970 --> 00:11:27,080
Manic disorder can make you delusional, impulsive,

128
00:11:27,080 --> 00:11:29,250
and makes you sleep less, too.

129
00:11:29,250 --> 00:11:32,220
It can cause eating disorders or shopping addiction.

130
00:11:32,220 --> 00:11:35,680
There are nine major symptoms of depression.

131
00:11:35,680 --> 00:11:38,210
Lack of sleep, too much sleep,

132
00:11:38,210 --> 00:11:42,080
difficulty to focus and make a decision...

133
00:11:43,010 --> 00:11:44,480
Ah Rin.

134
00:11:45,330 --> 00:11:47,720
I took her to the hospital.

135
00:11:48,950 --> 00:11:51,580
She's okay. Nothing's wrong with her.

136
00:11:51,580 --> 00:11:55,650
But I think Ah Rin noticed...

137
00:11:55,650 --> 00:11:59,090
that we're different than usual.

138
00:11:59,980 --> 00:12:02,000
She keeps asking for you.

139
00:12:02,750 --> 00:12:04,450
I think she's anxious.

140
00:12:06,330 --> 00:12:09,820
She just fell asleep after acting grumpy.

141
00:12:09,820 --> 00:12:11,200
Go to bed.

142
00:12:19,980 --> 00:12:22,610
Ah Rin, are you awake?

143
00:12:22,610 --> 00:12:24,240
Yes.

144
00:12:27,480 --> 00:12:29,060
Ah Rin.

145
00:12:29,060 --> 00:12:30,520
Yes?

146
00:12:33,430 --> 00:12:37,650
I'm sorry I've been so busy lately.

147
00:12:37,650 --> 00:12:40,160
Do you like going to work?

148
00:12:40,160 --> 00:12:41,420
Huh?

149
00:12:42,450 --> 00:12:43,660
Yes.

150
00:12:43,660 --> 00:12:49,180
Dad told me. That you're happy because you work.

151
00:12:50,480 --> 00:12:54,880
I'm happy if you're happy.

152
00:13:00,020 --> 00:13:03,060
Thank you for understanding.

153
00:13:03,060 --> 00:13:08,760
But don't go to work on my birthday and go play with me somewhere.

154
00:13:08,760 --> 00:13:11,700
With Mom, Dad, and Grandpa.

155
00:13:11,700 --> 00:13:14,450
We all need to go, okay?

156
00:13:16,810 --> 00:13:18,290
Okay.

157
00:13:19,500 --> 00:13:21,650
Yes. Let's.

158
00:13:21,650 --> 00:13:24,830
You mean it, right? You promised.

159
00:13:24,830 --> 00:13:27,200
Yes. Promise.

160
00:13:30,310 --> 00:13:32,390
[Do not enter - Police - Under investigation]

161
00:13:45,240 --> 00:13:46,780
Ms. Seo.

162
00:13:48,120 --> 00:13:52,310
I'm sorry to call late, but I need to tell you something.

163
00:14:05,640 --> 00:14:09,290
[CEO Seo Jae Won]

164
00:14:09,510 --> 00:14:13,220
I heard from Secretary Kim about Baek Seung Gyu's accident.

165
00:14:13,220 --> 00:14:15,920
And that you took him to the hospital...

166
00:14:18,540 --> 00:14:20,360
It was that day, right?

167
00:14:21,190 --> 00:14:23,620
The day I almost got into an accident.

168
00:14:24,770 --> 00:14:26,650
Why didn't you tell me?

169
00:14:26,650 --> 00:14:27,980
I needed to confirm.

170
00:14:27,980 --> 00:14:29,910
Confirm what?

171
00:14:31,310 --> 00:14:33,330
Tell me.

172
00:14:33,330 --> 00:14:36,030
Everything you're hiding from me.

173
00:14:36,030 --> 00:14:37,160
What is it?

174
00:14:37,160 --> 00:14:39,260
What if I did?

175
00:14:39,260 --> 00:14:40,950
And then what?

176
00:14:41,720 --> 00:14:44,220
What can you do?

177
00:14:44,220 --> 00:14:47,560
You almost died twice, but you couldn't do anything.

178
00:14:47,560 --> 00:14:52,360
Does Baek Seung Gyu have to do with what happened to me?

179
00:14:54,370 --> 00:14:56,520
Let's go to the police station now.

180
00:14:56,520 --> 00:14:57,750
I'll tell them everything.

181
00:14:57,750 --> 00:14:58,910
No.

182
00:14:58,910 --> 00:15:00,890
Why not?

183
00:15:00,890 --> 00:15:05,480
You can't trust anyone, and you're anxious every day. Why try to keep it a secret?

184
00:15:05,480 --> 00:15:07,440
What is it for?

185
00:15:07,440 --> 00:15:10,440
What do you want to protect so much?

186
00:15:11,620 --> 00:15:14,720
- Ms. Seo.
- I'm trying to protect everyone.

187
00:15:14,720 --> 00:15:17,610
My family and work.

188
00:15:17,610 --> 00:15:19,920
I can't give up on either.

189
00:15:19,920 --> 00:15:21,520
Please.

190
00:15:21,520 --> 00:15:23,990
Protect Seo Jae Won first.

191
00:15:25,120 --> 00:15:26,830
Let's stop.

192
00:15:30,970 --> 00:15:33,130
Seung Gyu is the stalker.

193
00:15:33,850 --> 00:15:36,180
The one who broke into the office that day.

194
00:15:38,770 --> 00:15:44,100
And Heo Chi Yeong was the first one he talked to after leaving the office.

195
00:16:00,060 --> 00:16:01,870
Isn't that Seo Jae Won?

196
00:16:01,870 --> 00:16:03,480
It's her, right?

197
00:16:05,120 --> 00:16:06,720
It is.

198
00:16:16,800 --> 00:16:18,540
Welcome.

199
00:16:26,610 --> 00:16:28,040
Heo Chi Yeong?

200
00:16:28,040 --> 00:16:29,700
Have you talked to him recently?

201
00:16:29,700 --> 00:16:30,980
When was the last time you talked to him?

202
00:16:30,980 --> 00:16:33,200
Seung Gyu is the stalker.

203
00:16:33,200 --> 00:16:38,530
And Heo Chi Yeong was the first one he talked to after leaving the office.

204
00:16:38,530 --> 00:16:40,940
How come you never thought about looking for him?

205
00:16:40,940 --> 00:16:43,450
It's been 30 years since I talked to him.

206
00:16:43,450 --> 00:16:46,710
- How did it go?
- He's basically a stranger.

207
00:16:46,710 --> 00:16:48,740
Heo Chi Yeong.

208
00:16:48,740 --> 00:16:51,020
Why did Baek Seung Gyu stalk me?

209
00:16:52,540 --> 00:16:55,550
Here's the iced coffee you ordered.

210
00:17:52,590 --> 00:17:53,850
My goodness!

211
00:17:53,850 --> 00:17:56,100
Are you okay? My gosh!

212
00:17:56,940 --> 00:17:59,380
Gosh, ma'am. The blood.

213
00:17:59,380 --> 00:18:03,410
Hold on, hold on. What do I do? What do I do? Wait...

214
00:18:03,410 --> 00:18:06,900
Let me get the first aid kit. Just a moment.

215
00:18:12,300 --> 00:18:13,920
[Seo Yoon Jin]

216
00:18:18,900 --> 00:18:23,290
[Psychiatrist's Office 1]

217
00:18:23,290 --> 00:18:25,200
Oh, really?

218
00:18:37,330 --> 00:18:39,090
[Psychiatrist's Office]

219
00:19:00,600 --> 00:19:01,810
Are you sure?

220
00:19:01,810 --> 00:19:04,990
I said I definitely saw her.

221
00:19:04,990 --> 00:19:07,480
I always run into her in the hallway. It's so creepy.

222
00:19:07,480 --> 00:19:10,760
How do you think I feel? She's in my class.

223
00:19:10,760 --> 00:19:12,610
You must hate it.

224
00:19:33,910 --> 00:19:35,500
Excuse me.

225
00:19:37,570 --> 00:19:39,790
You dropped this.

226
00:19:41,020 --> 00:19:43,730
Hey, you have blood there.

227
00:19:48,230 --> 00:19:50,530
Do you want to borrow my gym shirt?

228
00:19:51,440 --> 00:19:53,070
Follow me.

229
00:19:53,070 --> 00:19:54,980
It's in the art studio.

230
00:19:59,800 --> 00:20:01,890
[Art Studio]

231
00:20:30,990 --> 00:20:34,000
Why? Are you interested?

232
00:20:35,080 --> 00:20:36,490
No.

233
00:20:37,160 --> 00:20:38,620
How's your arm?

234
00:20:39,400 --> 00:20:41,120
Is it okay?

235
00:20:42,500 --> 00:20:44,560
It's totally fine.

236
00:20:45,880 --> 00:20:48,020
You don't have to hide it.

237
00:20:49,660 --> 00:20:52,330
I'm like this, too. My dad hit me.

238
00:20:52,330 --> 00:20:53,820
Why?

239
00:20:53,820 --> 00:20:56,310
Because I won second place in a competition.

240
00:20:57,500 --> 00:21:00,150
Isn't second place good?

241
00:21:00,950 --> 00:21:03,000
My dad doesn't think so.

242
00:21:03,000 --> 00:21:07,120
He said it's useless unless you win first place.

243
00:21:10,410 --> 00:21:12,250
Isn't that so annoying?

244
00:21:17,100 --> 00:21:18,880
Was that kind of funny?

245
00:21:20,180 --> 00:21:21,370
A little?

246
00:21:21,370 --> 00:21:22,880
A little?

247
00:21:30,850 --> 00:21:33,080
The wound is deep.

248
00:21:33,900 --> 00:21:36,300
You should go to the hospital.

249
00:21:38,730 --> 00:21:42,780
Being on meds doesn't change a lot of things.

250
00:21:42,780 --> 00:21:48,630
It just makes the rollercoaster-like mood swing a little less severe.

251
00:21:48,630 --> 00:21:51,380
Why don't you take the medicine?

252
00:21:51,380 --> 00:21:54,780
It doesn't let you think deeply.

253
00:21:54,780 --> 00:21:58,040
What do you need to think about being off meds?

254
00:21:59,660 --> 00:22:02,150
You have a hunch about something, right?

255
00:22:03,970 --> 00:22:06,070
I mean Heo Chi Yeong.

256
00:22:13,040 --> 00:22:15,320
[Seorin Hospital]

257
00:22:29,010 --> 00:22:30,070
How did it go?

258
00:22:30,070 --> 00:22:35,080
Heo Chi Yeong's last visit was in 2015.

259
00:22:35,080 --> 00:22:37,830
I guess he suffered from a chronic lung disease.

260
00:22:37,830 --> 00:22:40,270
He always visited alone without a guardian.

261
00:22:40,270 --> 00:22:42,710
He never mentioned having a brother, either.

262
00:22:43,480 --> 00:22:46,980
He was getting progressively worse, but there was no one to care for him.

263
00:22:46,980 --> 00:22:49,650
He said he'd go to a nursing hospital on his own.

264
00:22:49,650 --> 00:22:52,700
Check the nursing hospitals nearby, then.

265
00:22:52,700 --> 00:22:54,230
Okay.

266
00:22:56,910 --> 00:22:59,270
Why is everything so easy?

267
00:23:02,050 --> 00:23:07,160
How much will she pay me that she's bossing me around?

268
00:23:23,930 --> 00:23:26,460
What's this? What are you doing?

269
00:23:26,460 --> 00:23:28,440
I'm installing CCTVs.

270
00:23:28,440 --> 00:23:30,330
We finished installing.

271
00:23:30,330 --> 00:23:32,370
- The child's room is upstairs.
- Okay.

272
00:23:32,370 --> 00:23:34,230
What are the CCTVs for suddenly?

273
00:23:34,230 --> 00:23:36,900
I can't relax because I'm worried about Ah Rin.

274
00:23:36,900 --> 00:23:39,680
Geez, I'm home. Why do you worry?

275
00:23:39,680 --> 00:23:42,020
I'm worried even though you're around.

276
00:23:42,870 --> 00:23:45,740
Gosh. Seriously.

277
00:23:47,020 --> 00:23:50,430
Jae Won, why are you doing this?

278
00:23:50,430 --> 00:23:51,850
You're acting so strangely.

279
00:23:51,850 --> 00:23:53,400
What did I do, anyway?

280
00:23:53,400 --> 00:23:55,840
What are you thinking exactly?

281
00:23:55,840 --> 00:23:59,650
How long do I have to keep up with your erratic mood swings?

282
00:23:59,650 --> 00:24:01,810
I feel so suffocated.

283
00:24:03,030 --> 00:24:05,460
It's for our family.

284
00:24:26,310 --> 00:24:28,220
Hold it, please.

285
00:24:34,700 --> 00:24:36,450
Is it going well?

286
00:24:40,310 --> 00:24:44,100
Who's the person you've been seeing lately?

287
00:24:48,260 --> 00:24:50,350
Why are you curious about that?

288
00:24:55,510 --> 00:24:57,400
He's just an office worker.

289
00:24:59,310 --> 00:25:01,670
Won't you introduce him to me?

290
00:25:03,170 --> 00:25:04,220
Why would I?

291
00:25:04,220 --> 00:25:07,580
You always introduced your new boyfriends to me.

292
00:25:07,580 --> 00:25:11,100
Is it somehow different this time?

293
00:25:11,100 --> 00:25:12,770
Maybe.

294
00:25:13,770 --> 00:25:18,360
All of you will be shocked if you see him.

295
00:25:24,580 --> 00:25:27,510
You're making me even more curious.

296
00:25:30,140 --> 00:25:31,650
Carry on, then.

297
00:25:43,710 --> 00:25:45,310
"All of you"?

298
00:26:13,110 --> 00:26:16,180
[Heo Soon Yeong]

299
00:26:21,850 --> 00:26:24,550
Yes, come on in.

300
00:26:31,220 --> 00:26:33,180
Long time no see.

301
00:26:34,100 --> 00:26:36,260
Excuse me for a moment, Te Oh.

302
00:26:37,080 --> 00:26:41,790
I'm so busy because I'll be teaching again next semester.

303
00:26:41,790 --> 00:26:44,590
I tried to finish quickly when I got your call.

304
00:26:48,800 --> 00:26:51,180
I'm all done now.

305
00:27:00,130 --> 00:27:02,460
I recommended him to Dereve.

306
00:27:02,460 --> 00:27:05,720
He has good taste and is passionate.

307
00:27:05,720 --> 00:27:10,910
Seung Gyu can show off his talent if you lead him well.

308
00:27:10,910 --> 00:27:13,550
I wonder if he'd get a chance.

309
00:27:14,290 --> 00:27:16,450
He's at the hospital right now.

310
00:27:16,450 --> 00:27:20,650
He fell from his apartment building.

311
00:27:22,260 --> 00:27:23,600
Pardon?

312
00:27:25,950 --> 00:27:27,700
Wait, how...

313
00:27:27,700 --> 00:27:31,200
We're trying to find out what happened.

314
00:27:33,590 --> 00:27:35,150
Tomorrow...

315
00:27:35,150 --> 00:27:37,390
See you at school tomorrow.

316
00:27:37,390 --> 00:27:40,620
I need to tell you something about Ms. Seo.

317
00:27:40,620 --> 00:27:42,740
You must come.

318
00:27:48,750 --> 00:27:49,770
[Baek Seung Gyu]

319
00:27:55,620 --> 00:27:57,290
Hello?

320
00:27:57,290 --> 00:28:00,200
Seung Gyu, what happened?

321
00:28:07,540 --> 00:28:09,840
Did you call him not knowing what happened?

322
00:28:11,810 --> 00:28:17,200
I did call him to ask about something regarding school.

323
00:28:17,200 --> 00:28:18,850
I guess it was a very urgent matter.

324
00:28:18,850 --> 00:28:23,680
You didn't even have time to check who had answered your call.

325
00:28:28,120 --> 00:28:31,190
Is that why you're here?

326
00:28:31,190 --> 00:28:34,930
I'm sure the police will take care of the investigation.

327
00:28:36,810 --> 00:28:43,760
Or is there a reason why you personally have to do this on your own?

328
00:29:00,260 --> 00:29:03,360
Ms. Seo, I got a call from the repair shop.

329
00:29:03,360 --> 00:29:05,640
The car that was in the accident

330
00:29:05,640 --> 00:29:10,190
had a faulty brake pad, apparently.

331
00:29:10,190 --> 00:29:11,860
What caused it?

332
00:29:12,860 --> 00:29:14,740
There's no sign of tampering.

333
00:29:14,740 --> 00:29:17,950
They think it's because it wasn't changed on time.

334
00:29:17,950 --> 00:29:19,680
Are they really sure about that?

335
00:29:19,680 --> 00:29:22,770
I checked through a different shop, just in case.

336
00:29:32,790 --> 00:29:35,270
[Worn out brake pad]

337
00:29:35,270 --> 00:29:39,370
How about you hire a different driver?

338
00:29:41,550 --> 00:29:43,250
What else do you have?

339
00:29:43,250 --> 00:29:45,170
This is regarding a TV appearance.

340
00:29:45,170 --> 00:29:48,920
It's a family variety show. It's a popular show with a high rating.

341
00:29:49,920 --> 00:29:51,160
Family variety show?

342
00:29:51,160 --> 00:29:55,050
Yes. You'll have to shoot at home if you agree to it.

343
00:29:55,050 --> 00:29:57,710
With Professor Heo and Ah Rin, too.

344
00:29:58,870 --> 00:30:00,700
I'll think about it.

345
00:30:00,700 --> 00:30:03,330
I'll stop by the Gangnam store and go straight home.

346
00:30:03,330 --> 00:30:05,210
How about the car?

347
00:30:05,210 --> 00:30:07,130
I'll take mine.

348
00:30:20,450 --> 00:30:24,660
[Proposal for TV program guest appearance]

349
00:30:41,590 --> 00:30:43,100
- Ta-da.
- You're scary.

350
00:30:43,100 --> 00:30:45,870
It's Dad. It's Dad. I'm Dad now.

351
00:30:45,870 --> 00:30:47,660
No, I'm Dad now.

352
00:30:47,660 --> 00:30:50,440
- You have to hug me. It's Dad.
- Scary.

353
00:30:57,540 --> 00:30:59,530
I'll sleep in the study for a while.

354
00:30:59,530 --> 00:31:01,530
Don't worry about me and go to bed.

355
00:31:42,160 --> 00:31:45,630
I'm sure the police will take care of the investigation.

356
00:31:45,630 --> 00:31:52,060
Or is there a reason why you personally have to do this on your own?

357
00:31:53,720 --> 00:31:56,890
Where can I meet Heo Chi Yeong?

358
00:31:56,890 --> 00:32:00,390
I don't know. I'm looking for him, too.

359
00:32:01,780 --> 00:32:03,770
He went missing.

360
00:32:04,630 --> 00:32:06,400
Eight years ago.

361
00:32:21,850 --> 00:32:26,120
[Seo Jae Won's mentor, Kwon Yeong Ik, the chairman of Yein Foundation, showed support at the launch show]

362
00:32:32,160 --> 00:32:35,040
[List of VIP attendees at 2016 Dereve Launch Show]

363
00:32:49,490 --> 00:32:54,130
Ms. Seo has been absent from work often and

364
00:32:54,130 --> 00:32:55,920
has canceled important meetings.

365
00:32:55,920 --> 00:32:59,650
There have been complaints among employees.

366
00:32:59,650 --> 00:33:03,660
The sales have been slow since the falling incident, too.

367
00:33:04,490 --> 00:33:07,270
Something might need to be done.

368
00:33:07,970 --> 00:33:09,240
Like what?

369
00:33:09,240 --> 00:33:10,530
Well, that's-

370
00:33:10,530 --> 00:33:12,540
Seo Jae Won is Dereve.

371
00:33:12,540 --> 00:33:14,570
Do you have any alternatives?

372
00:33:15,270 --> 00:33:16,570
I didn't mean it like that.

373
00:33:16,570 --> 00:33:18,300
You can leave now.

374
00:33:20,650 --> 00:33:21,990
Okay.

375
00:33:33,740 --> 00:33:35,880
It's an article that will be published tomorrow.

376
00:33:40,210 --> 00:33:44,060
[Seo Jae Won's mentor, Kwon Yeong Ik, is the favored candidate as the minister of the Ministry of Culture]

377
00:34:19,230 --> 00:34:21,360
Say ah.

378
00:34:27,770 --> 00:34:31,080
What do you think of the fried rice I made?

379
00:34:31,080 --> 00:34:33,400
It's not too bad.

380
00:34:33,400 --> 00:34:36,310
Not too bad? Is that it?

381
00:34:36,310 --> 00:34:38,540
You're hurting my feelings.

382
00:34:38,540 --> 00:34:41,050
It's a little better than Mom's.

383
00:34:41,050 --> 00:34:42,550
Really?

384
00:34:42,550 --> 00:34:45,330
You're so sweet. That's enough for me. That's enough.

385
00:34:45,330 --> 00:34:47,350
Gosh, you're so sweet.

386
00:34:47,350 --> 00:34:50,000
Hush. You can't tell Mom, okay?

387
00:34:50,000 --> 00:34:51,230
Okay.

388
00:34:51,230 --> 00:34:53,320
- Okay.
- I heard everything.

389
00:34:54,490 --> 00:34:57,060
You didn't like the one I made, huh?

390
00:34:57,060 --> 00:35:00,200
I'll have to ask Dad to cook from now on.

391
00:35:00,200 --> 00:35:02,910
What do we do? I think she's upset.

392
00:35:03,760 --> 00:35:05,610
I'm sorry, Mom.

393
00:35:05,610 --> 00:35:08,920
What are you sorry for? Tell me more.

394
00:35:08,920 --> 00:35:12,290
I'm sorry, I can't lie.

395
00:35:13,380 --> 00:35:17,920
No, no, no. It's a great thing that you don't lie.

396
00:35:17,920 --> 00:35:22,660
Ah Rin, I make tasty food and play with you every day.

397
00:35:22,660 --> 00:35:24,860
You like Dad a lot more than Mom, right?

398
00:35:24,860 --> 00:35:27,520
I don't think so. You like Mom more, right?

399
00:35:27,520 --> 00:35:29,940
I don't think so. You tell us, Ah Rin.

400
00:35:29,940 --> 00:35:31,480
Who do you like more between Mon and Dad?

401
00:35:31,480 --> 00:35:33,130
You prefer Mom, right?

402
00:35:33,130 --> 00:35:35,180
You prefer Dad, right?

403
00:35:35,950 --> 00:35:39,590
I can't hang out with you because you're too childish.

404
00:35:40,870 --> 00:35:43,390
You hurt my feelings again.

405
00:35:43,390 --> 00:35:44,800
I'll go to work now.

406
00:35:44,800 --> 00:35:46,680
See you.

407
00:35:46,680 --> 00:35:48,430
Okay.

408
00:35:48,430 --> 00:35:50,070
See you later.

409
00:35:50,070 --> 00:35:52,660
Keep eating. I'll see Mom off.

410
00:35:52,660 --> 00:35:54,170
Jae Won.

411
00:35:55,170 --> 00:35:57,600
You're coming home early today, right?

412
00:35:57,600 --> 00:35:59,300
I will.

413
00:36:00,370 --> 00:36:02,090
Let me hug you.

414
00:36:05,880 --> 00:36:07,660
Have a good day.

415
00:36:15,690 --> 00:36:17,710
Okay. See you later.

416
00:36:17,710 --> 00:36:18,810
Okay.

417
00:36:18,810 --> 00:36:22,530
Okay! That's a wrap. Thank you. Thank you.

418
00:36:22,530 --> 00:36:25,340
- Thank you.
- Well done.

419
00:36:26,600 --> 00:36:30,120
You're a family of entertainers.

420
00:36:30,120 --> 00:36:32,220
I think our viewers will react positively.

421
00:36:32,220 --> 00:36:34,610
That's good to hear.

422
00:36:34,610 --> 00:36:35,990
So I was thinking...

423
00:36:35,990 --> 00:36:42,630
maybe we could show more of the father playing with Ah Rin.

424
00:36:42,630 --> 00:36:46,510
We can air for two weeks if we get enough footage.

425
00:36:50,590 --> 00:36:53,160
Sounds good. Let's do that.

426
00:36:54,380 --> 00:36:55,620
Could we talk for a second?

427
00:36:55,620 --> 00:36:57,200
Okay, let's.

428
00:36:58,080 --> 00:37:00,060
The group shot was great.

429
00:37:00,060 --> 00:37:04,130
You need to leave for the buyer meeting now, Ms. Seo.

430
00:37:04,130 --> 00:37:05,410
Okay.

431
00:37:06,110 --> 00:37:10,070
I can go by myself. Please stay and keep an eye on them.

432
00:37:10,070 --> 00:37:12,070
Care for Ah Rin, too.

433
00:37:12,070 --> 00:37:13,470
Okay.

434
00:37:17,700 --> 00:37:21,940
Hello, Ms. Seo. I'm Park Yong Jin, your new driver.

435
00:37:34,950 --> 00:37:38,120
The police already took the CCTV files.

436
00:37:39,050 --> 00:37:40,640
Could you tell me when that was?

437
00:37:40,640 --> 00:37:43,760
The same day the man from the fifth floor fell.

438
00:37:43,760 --> 00:37:45,020
Do you have a copy, by chance?

439
00:37:45,020 --> 00:37:47,040
We don't have such a thing.

440
00:37:47,040 --> 00:37:49,500
Did they say they'd return it, then?

441
00:37:49,500 --> 00:37:53,840
No. They asked for it in a rush. I didn't get to bring it up.

442
00:38:01,690 --> 00:38:03,310
Please be punctual.

443
00:38:03,310 --> 00:38:04,820
Did you bring what I requested?

444
00:38:04,820 --> 00:38:07,110
There are so many people here. Do you have to do this?

445
00:38:07,110 --> 00:38:11,210
That's why I made you come here instead of me going to the police station.

446
00:38:11,210 --> 00:38:13,180
So you don't get into trouble.

447
00:38:13,180 --> 00:38:15,610
Gosh, shit.

448
00:38:18,310 --> 00:38:19,650
Here.

449
00:38:26,330 --> 00:38:29,440
You said the last time was final.

450
00:38:30,890 --> 00:38:33,330
I mean it this time.

451
00:38:33,330 --> 00:38:35,180
Geez.

452
00:38:35,180 --> 00:38:37,720
I took some pocket money. What's the big deal?

453
00:38:37,720 --> 00:38:42,120
Hyungnim, how long do you think you could drag me around? Huh?

454
00:38:42,120 --> 00:38:45,030
Let's face it. You're not even a detective anymore.

455
00:38:45,030 --> 00:38:50,250
Just keep selling insurance. Why poke around everywhere?

456
00:38:50,250 --> 00:38:52,740
Geez. You got fired acting this way, too.

457
00:38:52,740 --> 00:38:54,570
You got more talkative.

458
00:38:55,250 --> 00:38:57,840
Anyway, I can't this time.

459
00:38:58,730 --> 00:39:03,290
I kept track of all the threats you made.

460
00:39:03,290 --> 00:39:05,570
I could easily use it to-

461
00:39:08,110 --> 00:39:10,170
How dare you!

462
00:39:13,190 --> 00:39:15,780
Shut up, you bastard.

463
00:39:26,120 --> 00:39:30,300
I'll use it for a few days and return it. Just wait.

464
00:39:38,100 --> 00:39:39,850
Hello, Ms. Seo Jae Won.

465
00:39:39,850 --> 00:39:41,600
How's everything going?

466
00:39:41,600 --> 00:39:44,200
Well, it's not so easy.

467
00:39:44,230 --> 00:39:47,060
I checked all the nursing hospitals.

468
00:39:47,060 --> 00:39:49,470
They couldn't find anyone named Heo Chi Yeong.

469
00:39:49,470 --> 00:39:54,350
I think we should check nursing homes or something like that.

470
00:39:54,350 --> 00:39:56,040
Please continue.

471
00:39:56,040 --> 00:39:57,610
Okay.

472
00:40:12,630 --> 00:40:16,340
Detective Lee, let me ask you one more thing.

473
00:40:16,340 --> 00:40:19,480
Try looking for this person in a week.

474
00:40:19,480 --> 00:40:22,320
There's information on the back of the photo.

475
00:40:22,320 --> 00:40:25,020
Try checking nursing facilities.

476
00:40:29,840 --> 00:40:31,500
And you...

477
00:40:32,400 --> 00:40:34,760
You'd better start talking less.

478
00:40:34,760 --> 00:40:36,000
You know?

479
00:40:36,020 --> 00:40:40,110
Getting fired won't be the end of it if you keep blabbering like that.

480
00:40:40,110 --> 00:40:42,550
You'll die by my hands.

481
00:40:42,550 --> 00:40:43,900
Okay.

482
00:40:48,590 --> 00:40:50,620
Jae Won.

483
00:40:50,620 --> 00:40:52,300
You're coming home early today, right?

484
00:40:52,300 --> 00:40:53,970
I will.

485
00:40:53,970 --> 00:40:55,630
Let me hug you.

486
00:40:58,660 --> 00:41:00,610
Have a good day.

487
00:41:00,610 --> 00:41:02,200
Okay.

488
00:41:04,280 --> 00:41:05,940
See you later.

489
00:41:18,010 --> 00:41:19,720
Yes, I'll give you a call immediately afterward.

490
00:41:19,720 --> 00:41:23,740
I can't tell you when it'll be shipped since we're receiving a lot of orders.

491
00:41:23,740 --> 00:41:26,040
The server went down because of high traffic.

492
00:41:26,040 --> 00:41:27,670
You need to get it fixed immediately.

493
00:41:27,670 --> 00:41:29,630
Excuse me one moment.

494
00:41:29,630 --> 00:41:31,060
Can we keep taking orders?

495
00:41:31,060 --> 00:41:32,390
Where's the production team leader?

496
00:41:32,390 --> 00:41:34,600
He's reporting to Ms. Seo.

497
00:41:35,670 --> 00:41:38,250
All the products that were in the show are sold out.

498
00:41:38,250 --> 00:41:42,500
We'll hire extra people tomorrow to expand the production line as much as possible.

499
00:41:42,500 --> 00:41:46,570
Please check the inventory for the products that will be in the show next week, too.

500
00:41:46,570 --> 00:41:48,720
Okay, got it.

501
00:41:51,080 --> 00:41:56,260
We keep getting requests for interviews and TV appearances since the show was received well.

502
00:41:56,260 --> 00:41:59,570
I should do as much as possible if it helps with our PR.

503
00:41:59,570 --> 00:42:01,000
The thing is...

504
00:42:01,000 --> 00:42:04,990
they want both you and Professor Heo.

505
00:42:06,730 --> 00:42:08,290
All right.

506
00:42:10,370 --> 00:42:12,030
Seong Hee.

507
00:42:13,760 --> 00:42:14,960
Yes?

508
00:42:14,960 --> 00:42:17,530
You can take a break if you're tired.

509
00:42:18,470 --> 00:42:20,450
I'm okay.

510
00:42:48,210 --> 00:42:51,640
Do you know how the investigation is going?

511
00:42:51,640 --> 00:42:55,130
Would they be able to catch the culprit?

512
00:42:56,130 --> 00:42:58,640
Do you think there's a culprit?

513
00:42:58,640 --> 00:43:00,470
Do you know anything, by chance?

514
00:43:00,470 --> 00:43:02,410
I don't, but...

515
00:43:03,350 --> 00:43:08,120
I'm certain he didn't do that on his own.

516
00:43:10,640 --> 00:43:12,100
However...

517
00:43:13,660 --> 00:43:16,170
there's something that bothers me.

518
00:43:23,070 --> 00:43:24,670
I'll be right back.

519
00:43:37,420 --> 00:43:39,660
How long will you do this?

520
00:43:40,480 --> 00:43:43,250
I did as much as I could!

521
00:43:46,020 --> 00:43:50,240
No, no! This isn't right.

522
00:43:51,370 --> 00:43:55,690
I mean, this makes no sense at all.

523
00:43:57,470 --> 00:43:59,430
I've never seen him...

524
00:43:59,430 --> 00:44:01,250
getting that angry.

525
00:44:01,250 --> 00:44:02,760
When was that?

526
00:44:02,760 --> 00:44:04,610
Do you remember the date?

527
00:44:39,660 --> 00:44:40,860
Hello?

528
00:44:40,860 --> 00:44:42,850
I found Heo Chi Yeong.

529
00:44:42,850 --> 00:44:44,630
I texted you the address.

530
00:44:44,630 --> 00:44:46,080
Okay.

531
00:44:49,200 --> 00:44:50,850
Where are you going?

532
00:45:17,380 --> 00:45:19,070
Let me drive you.

533
00:45:20,260 --> 00:45:21,910
Let's take my car.

534
00:45:24,550 --> 00:45:26,460
I thought you were in a hurry.

535
00:45:43,820 --> 00:45:47,040
[Seongshinwol Nursing Home]

536
00:45:49,040 --> 00:45:51,340
Don't wait for me. You can leave.

537
00:46:02,570 --> 00:46:04,350
Hello.

538
00:46:04,400 --> 00:46:06,700
How can I help you?

539
00:46:06,720 --> 00:46:09,410
I'm here to see Mr. Heo Chi Yeong.

540
00:46:23,210 --> 00:46:25,340
You should've come sooner.

541
00:46:25,340 --> 00:46:29,340
He struggled with pain while he was here,

542
00:46:29,340 --> 00:46:33,460
but he seemed more hurt by the fact that his family abandoned him.

543
00:46:40,100 --> 00:46:43,830
Get in. I won't ask you anything.

544
00:46:51,000 --> 00:46:54,470
[Seongshinwol Nursing Home]

545
00:47:10,220 --> 00:47:14,230
Don't tell Secretary Kim about what Baek Seung Gyu did.

546
00:47:16,770 --> 00:47:20,540
The fact that a loved one has another side of them

547
00:47:21,870 --> 00:47:25,080
will make anyone go through hell.

548
00:47:25,080 --> 00:47:27,820
You think not knowing is okay?

549
00:47:27,820 --> 00:47:30,760
Even though she won't know his true self?

550
00:47:33,790 --> 00:47:36,550
No matter how close you are to someone,

551
00:47:37,550 --> 00:47:39,810
you can't know everything.

552
00:47:41,130 --> 00:47:46,740
Even married couples who share a blanket have secrets.

553
00:47:51,090 --> 00:47:54,200
If nothing changes by knowing,

554
00:47:55,950 --> 00:47:57,840
it's better not to know.

555
00:47:59,190 --> 00:48:01,590
Have you tried to change?

556
00:48:02,930 --> 00:48:06,040
Get away from reality if it's hellish.

557
00:48:06,040 --> 00:48:07,830
I'll help you.

558
00:49:52,530 --> 00:49:55,220
The sales went up more than 250%.

559
00:49:55,220 --> 00:49:57,170
Not to mention the storefronts,

560
00:49:57,170 --> 00:50:00,050
the online store is attracting more visitors.

561
00:50:00,050 --> 00:50:01,380
Since we're on the topic,

562
00:50:01,380 --> 00:50:07,180
why don't we revisit the factory expansion plan we paused last year?

563
00:50:07,180 --> 00:50:09,710
I already got a lot of investment offers.

564
00:50:09,710 --> 00:50:11,250
Okay. I'll look into it.

565
00:50:11,250 --> 00:50:12,620
Okay.

566
00:50:14,320 --> 00:50:15,770
What's this?

567
00:50:15,770 --> 00:50:17,680
Who wants this?

568
00:50:21,280 --> 00:50:24,050
Ah Rin, isn't that your mom?

569
00:50:24,050 --> 00:50:25,960
No, it's not.

570
00:50:25,960 --> 00:50:29,510
My mom is really busy.

571
00:50:29,510 --> 00:50:31,250
No, it's her.

572
00:50:31,250 --> 00:50:33,770
I saw her on TV.

573
00:50:33,770 --> 00:50:35,290
It's not her, I said.

574
00:50:35,290 --> 00:50:36,560
Look.

575
00:50:36,560 --> 00:50:39,070
Gosh! Daebak.

576
00:50:41,210 --> 00:50:43,630
Aigoo, yes. What did you do?

577
00:50:43,630 --> 00:50:45,660
Did you play with the sand?

578
00:50:52,410 --> 00:50:55,990
Ah Rin. Grandpa is almost here.

579
00:50:55,990 --> 00:50:58,430
I'll go fishing with Grandpa.

580
00:50:58,430 --> 00:51:01,400
I'll catch a huge fish, Mom.

581
00:51:01,400 --> 00:51:05,050
I'll be looking forward to it. Have fun.

582
00:51:06,550 --> 00:51:09,040
- Bye, bye.
- Bye.

583
00:51:09,040 --> 00:51:10,080
Thank you in advance.

584
00:51:10,080 --> 00:51:12,800
Okay. I'll see her off.

585
00:51:15,030 --> 00:51:17,550
I'll be right back.

586
00:51:51,920 --> 00:51:53,590
Who is it?

587
00:51:58,970 --> 00:52:00,820
I can go in, right?

588
00:52:26,870 --> 00:52:28,780
How did you find my place?

589
00:52:28,780 --> 00:52:32,320
I told Mr. Kwon that I wanted to treat him to dinner.

590
00:52:32,320 --> 00:52:35,460
He gave me your address so I can bring you, too.

591
00:52:36,950 --> 00:52:39,820
Wait here. I'll talk to him for a second.

592
00:52:39,820 --> 00:52:41,220
Why?

593
00:52:42,220 --> 00:52:45,680
Will you tell him we had a falling out?

594
00:52:47,740 --> 00:52:50,300
He'd be disappointed.

595
00:52:50,300 --> 00:52:52,860
That's what you hate the most.

596
00:52:54,420 --> 00:52:56,870
Disappointing your father.

597
00:53:06,180 --> 00:53:08,380
It's been so long, Jae Won.

598
00:53:08,380 --> 00:53:11,390
I'm sorry. I should've visited you more often.

599
00:53:11,390 --> 00:53:15,330
It's okay. We know how busy you are.

600
00:53:15,330 --> 00:53:16,580
Where's Mr. Kwon?

601
00:53:16,580 --> 00:53:19,620
He said he's almost here.

602
00:53:19,620 --> 00:53:21,190
Honey.

603
00:53:23,530 --> 00:53:26,440
I'm sorry. Am I too late?

604
00:53:28,400 --> 00:53:32,050
CEO Seo. Have a seat.

605
00:53:45,740 --> 00:53:52,890
Dean Choi said she could look forward to getting hired as a full-time professor this time.

606
00:53:52,890 --> 00:53:54,940
Dean Choi from Yoon Jin's school?

607
00:53:55,710 --> 00:53:57,480
It must've been difficult persuading him.

608
00:53:57,480 --> 00:54:00,010
Yoon Jin has been an assistant professor for a long time.

609
00:54:00,770 --> 00:54:03,280
Gosh, that's so wonderful.

610
00:54:03,280 --> 00:54:05,590
Aren't you helping her too much?

611
00:54:05,590 --> 00:54:08,770
Does she even deserve it?

612
00:54:08,770 --> 00:54:11,120
Gosh, come on, Honey.

613
00:54:11,990 --> 00:54:14,090
You did the same for me.

614
00:54:14,090 --> 00:54:16,240
When I was in middle school,

615
00:54:17,240 --> 00:54:22,450
you had faith in me, supported me, and invested in me.

616
00:54:22,450 --> 00:54:24,450
It's for the same reason.

617
00:54:26,660 --> 00:54:28,920
The same reason?

618
00:54:30,030 --> 00:54:32,520
Is she holding something over your head?

619
00:54:32,520 --> 00:54:33,910
Pardon?

620
00:54:37,410 --> 00:54:39,680
I'm kidding. I'm kidding.

621
00:54:40,700 --> 00:54:45,840
I loved the look in your eyes then.

622
00:54:47,470 --> 00:54:49,520
Shouldn't we get a bottle of champagne?

623
00:54:49,520 --> 00:54:51,870
I ordered it already.

624
00:54:53,280 --> 00:54:54,940
Excuse me.

625
00:54:57,840 --> 00:54:59,240
Where are you?

626
00:55:00,000 --> 00:55:01,780
Okay. Hurry up.

627
00:55:02,780 --> 00:55:05,270
Is someone coming?

628
00:55:34,240 --> 00:55:36,850
You should've given me a heads-up.

629
00:55:52,710 --> 00:55:55,080
What happened to the other bow?

630
00:55:55,860 --> 00:55:58,880
You still look pretty.

631
00:56:03,680 --> 00:56:05,560
You mean the video was edited?

632
00:56:05,560 --> 00:56:07,470
Please have a look at this.

633
00:56:08,310 --> 00:56:09,720
What's this?

634
00:56:09,720 --> 00:56:12,340
It's Heo Chi Yeong's medical history.

635
00:56:12,340 --> 00:56:15,790
He would've suffered without a respirator in this condition.

636
00:56:17,480 --> 00:56:19,050
When was the last time you talked to him?

637
00:56:19,050 --> 00:56:21,540
I don't know. I don't even remember.

638
00:56:22,690 --> 00:56:27,910
I haven't talked to him since I was 13, when my parents divorced. It's been 30 years since I talked to him.

639
00:56:27,910 --> 00:56:31,740
So, where's Mr. Heo right now?

640
00:56:31,740 --> 00:56:34,380
He passed away last year.

641
00:56:38,200 --> 00:56:42,840
His younger brother came and even had a funeral. You had no idea?

642
00:57:02,340 --> 00:57:04,310
I invited him.

643
00:57:05,310 --> 00:57:08,700
We should all celebrate this happy occasion.

644
00:57:08,700 --> 00:57:09,830
It's okay, right?

645
00:57:09,830 --> 00:57:11,510
Of course.

646
00:57:11,510 --> 00:57:12,990
- Professor Heo.
- Yes.

647
00:57:12,990 --> 00:57:16,410
Didn't you walk by our foundation office recently?

648
00:57:16,410 --> 00:57:18,500
Your office?

649
00:57:18,500 --> 00:57:19,990
No.

650
00:57:19,990 --> 00:57:21,870
Maybe you were mistaken.

651
00:57:21,870 --> 00:57:23,700
Really?

652
00:57:23,700 --> 00:57:28,020
You could've said he was your twin.

653
00:57:29,560 --> 00:57:31,770
Are you sure it wasn't you?

654
00:57:31,770 --> 00:57:34,410
Come on. Not you, too.

655
00:57:35,410 --> 00:57:37,490
Have you been well, Ma'am?

656
00:57:37,490 --> 00:57:39,350
You got even more handsome.

657
00:57:39,350 --> 00:57:40,900
Thank you.

658
00:57:43,060 --> 00:57:45,050
Long time no see, Yoon Jin.

659
00:57:45,050 --> 00:57:48,040
Yes. Hello.

660
00:57:52,900 --> 00:57:56,770
I think Yoon Jin get promoted as a full-time professor soon.

661
00:57:56,770 --> 00:57:58,550
You should congratulate her, too.

662
00:57:58,550 --> 00:58:01,690
Is that why you told me to pick up champagne?

663
00:58:02,600 --> 00:58:04,520
Congratulations, Yoon Jin.

664
00:58:06,660 --> 00:58:08,640
Thank you.

665
00:58:16,240 --> 00:58:18,820
Shall we drink, then?

666
00:58:19,800 --> 00:58:21,590
Cheers.

667
00:58:30,100 --> 00:58:33,790
Yoon Jin needs to find someone like Professor Heo, too.

668
00:58:33,790 --> 00:58:36,980
Don't worry. She's already seeing him.

669
00:58:38,790 --> 00:58:40,540
What did you say?

670
00:58:53,700 --> 00:58:56,540
Someone like Professor Heo, I mean.

671
00:58:59,760 --> 00:59:02,630
She's dating someone.

672
00:59:05,310 --> 00:59:07,010
Is that true?

673
00:59:10,840 --> 00:59:12,930
Should I not have said it?

674
00:59:14,250 --> 00:59:16,540
Haven't you told them yet?

675
00:59:28,600 --> 00:59:30,400
Well, we're just...

676
00:59:31,420 --> 00:59:33,790
dating casually.

677
00:59:35,450 --> 00:59:37,900
Introduce us some time.

678
01:00:03,890 --> 01:00:06,380
One, two, three.

679
01:00:07,640 --> 01:00:09,600
Thank you.

680
01:00:55,500 --> 01:00:57,890
You must be tired. Go take a shower.

681
01:00:57,890 --> 01:00:59,330
Okay.

682
01:01:04,770 --> 01:01:06,970
Who's been calling you?

683
01:01:06,970 --> 01:01:08,710
It's a friend.

684
01:01:08,710 --> 01:01:10,260
Sang Won.

685
01:01:11,130 --> 01:01:14,760
He keeps asking me to join him for a drink.

686
01:01:22,500 --> 01:01:25,290
I'll have to step out for a second.

687
01:01:27,340 --> 01:01:29,200
This late?

688
01:01:29,200 --> 01:01:31,990
Yes. I guess he's really drunk.

689
01:01:31,990 --> 01:01:34,770
I'll be right back. He keeps calling me.

690
01:01:35,460 --> 01:01:38,210
Who does he want to see so badly?

691
01:01:40,760 --> 01:01:42,530
Heo Soon Yeong?

692
01:01:42,530 --> 01:01:44,560
Heo Chi Yeong?

693
01:01:44,560 --> 01:01:46,640
Or both?

694
01:01:51,690 --> 01:01:55,920
You'd better stop seeing Kwon Yoon Jin.

695
